        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: SNAP-25-binding protein enriched in neurons and exclusively located on synaptic vesicle membranes.. Experimental description: Results Fig.2: \"**Rat** tissue homogenates (50 μg protein per lane) and solubilized synaptosome preparation (10μg per lane) were immunoblotted with the Snapin antibody. Bands were visualized by ECL. (b) Distribution of Snapin in subcellular fractions of **rat** brain synaptosomes.\"" ;
